  "text": "The audit logging implementation in kubernetes/kubernetes spans four main areas within staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver:\n\n1. **Audit event creation** (`pkg/audit/request.go`): Creates audit Event objects from HTTP requests, populating user info, source IPs, verbs, resource info, and request/response bodies. `pkg/audit/context.go` manages the audit context attached to each request.\n\n2. **Policy evaluation** (`pkg/audit/policy/checker.go`, `policy/reader.go`, `policy/util.go`): Implements PolicyRuleEvaluator that matches requests against audit policy rules to determine audit level (None/Metadata/Request/RequestResponse). The evaluator interface is defined in `pkg/audit/evaluator.go`.\n\n3. **Backend dispatch** (`plugin/pkg/audit/log/backend.go` for log-file backend, `plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go` for webhook backend, `plugin/pkg/audit/buffered/buffered.go` for async buffering). The `pkg/audit/types.go` defines Backend/Sink interfaces, `pkg/audit/union.go` fans out events to multiple backends. `pkg/server/options/audit.go` wires up backends from CLI flags.\n\n4. **Truncation** (`plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go`): Wraps a backend to enforce maximum event size by truncating large request/response bodies.\n\nThe HTTP filter chain integration lives in `pkg/endpoints/filters/audit.go` (WithAudit handler), `audit_init.go` (audit ID and context init), and `authn_audit.go` (authentication-phase audit annotations). Supporting files include `pkg/audit/metrics.go`, `format.go`, `scheme.go`, and the API types at `pkg/apis/audit/types.go`.",
